items.name: TibiaWiki
items.title: TibiaWiki
items.headline: TibiaWiki - the english wiki about Tibia
items.desc: With over 15,000 pages, at TibiaWiki you will find information for practically everything that exists in Tibia. Whether you are looking for text of a book, want to know how to obtain a certain item, or need hints for a quest, we've got you covered. Some nice tools like the Outfiter, a minimap tool of whole Tibia and Loot Statistics make us worth your visit as well.

items.name: TibiaWikiPT
items.title: TibiaWikiPT
items.headline: TibiaWiki - a wiki brasileira sobre Tibia
items.desc: Com mais de 600 páginas, você vai encontrar praticamente tudo que sobre Tibia aqui na Tibia wiki. Se você estiver procurando texto de um livro, quiser saber como obter um certo item, ou precisar de dicas para uma missão, nós podemos te ajudar! Nós também temos estatísticas de Loot. Venha conferir e se divertir você também!

items.name: Kim Possible Wiki
items.title: Kim Possible Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Kim Possible Wiki
items.desc: The Kim Possible Wiki is a community created encyclopedia, which strives to be an exhaustive, professional quality, and accessible reference for everything related to the popular, award-winning series Kim Possible. Kim Possible was an American action/comedy series, produced by Disney, that followed the adventures of Kim Possible and her best friend, Ron Stoppable, as they dealt with high school and the freelance hero business. The wiki currently has hundreds of articles on the characters, episodes, locations, items, relationships, and missions featured in the Kim Possible universe.

items.name: Mission Impossible
items.title: Mission Impossible
items.headline: Welcome to the Mission Impossible wikia!
items.desc:
Mission: Impossible is an American television series which aired on the CBS network from September 1966 to March 1973. It returned to television for two seasons on ABC, from 1988 to 1990 and later inspired a blockbuster film series in the 1990s, 2000s, and 2010s.
This wiki is dedicated to the entire Mission: Impossible franchise, and strives to be the greatest fan-friendly M:I resource on the web.

items.name: Bible Wiki
items.title: Bible Wiki
items.headline: Bible Wikia: The Bible and Ancient History Wiki!
items.desc: Bible Wiki is a database covering people, places,books,doctrine and history of the Bible. Join us as we glorify God, write about the Bible and be in fellowship with other Christians.

items.name: Soulcalibur Wiki
items.title: Soulcalibur Wiki
items.headline: Soulcalibur Wiki
items.desc: Soulcalibur Wiki is a site based on the Soul series of fighting games developed by Namco. It has information on all of the aspects of each game, such as characters, various weapons, stages, secrets, and more.

items.name: The Tribe Wiki
items.title: The Tribe Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to The Tribe Wikia
items.desc: The Tribe is a New Zealand/British post-apocalyptic fictional TV series primarily aimed at teenagers. It is set in a near-future in which all adults have been wiped out by a deadly virus, leaving the children of the world to fend for themselves. The show's focus is on an unnamed city inhabited by tribes of children and teenagers. It was primarily filmed in and around Wellington, New Zealand.

items.name: Tibia Wiki
items.title: Tibia Wiki
items.headline: Tibia Wiki
items.desc: Este wiki está dedicado al videojuego Tibia, creado por CipSoft. El proyecto recopila información sobre este popular MMORPG ambientado en el mundo medieval de Tibia; donde a través de héroes clásicos como caballeros y magos se interactúa con centenares de miles de personas de todo el mundo.

items.name: Chibi Robo Wiki
items.title: Chibi Robo Wiki
items.headline: The Chibi-Robo wiki is about the best Nintendo game made.
items.desc: This wiki is about Chibi-Robo of course. He is the tiny robot that Nintendo loves if they put him in 4 games in all. He cooks, cleans, and saves your life? Yes he will save you from evil robots, trying to take your money and lives. Please watch out for him you might step on your best friend, he has a lot of sympathy for a robot that can't talk.

items.name: WikiBarn
items.title: WikiBarn
items.headline: Welcome to WikiBarn!
items.desc:
WikiBarn is a collaborative website about Barnyard and Back at the Barnyard, both the film and the video game. We welcome new users to come and help us edit our wikia!

The wiki format allows anyone to plant and harvest (i.e. create and edit) any article so that we can all work together to spread the word about WikiBarn; but we need your help as well!

items.desc: Biblioteka Arkanii jest projektem fan-fiction dotyczącym serii "Gwiezdne Wojny". Jest to jeden z największych tego typu projektów na polskiej Wikii. Gwarantujemy miłą administrację, przyjemną atmosferę i przede wszystkim wspaniałą zabawę!

items.name: Ibanez Wiki
items.title: Ibanez Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Ibanez Wiki
items.desc: Ibanez is a Japanese guitar brand owned by Hoshino Gakki. Based in Nagoya, Aichi, Japan, Hoshino Gakki were one of the first Japanese musical instrument companies to gain a significant foothold in import guitar sales in the United States and Europe.   The wiki covers all aspects of Ibanez guitars and all are welcome to contribute!

items.name: Tegami Bachi Wiki
items.title: Tegami Bachi Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Tegami Bachi Wiki
items.desc:
Tegami Bachi is the story of a young boy in a world called Amberground. The boy's name is Lag Seeing, and he dreams of becoming a Letter Bee because of Gauche Suede.

Gauche is Lag's rescuer. He is the Letter Bee that found young Lag Seeing marked as a letter in "Coza Bel", a small town in Yodaka (the lowest class district in Amberground). He has to deliver Lag to "Cambel Litus", a town in Yodaka, to join his aunt who was entrusted to take care of him.

items.title: Toribash Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Toribash Wiki!
items.desc:
Welcome to the Toribash wiki! Toribash is a turn-based 3D 3rd person tactical martial arts simulator using physics-based attacks, created by Hampus Soderstrom, a Swedish software developer. Toribash was a "Best Game Idea" finalist at the 2006 Swedish Game Awards.

The game is Freeware, and is still under development to this day with updates (and is currently at version 3.99). A WiiWare version was released in the PAL region on July 9th, 2010 and in North America on July 12th, 2010.
